# Confirms sleep_cpu() can be woken by a registered WDT_vect ISR handler
# (rather than the no-handler on_watchdog_reset callback path). wdt_enable
# (WDTO_250MS) means the first wake happens ~250ms in.
0.1, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "sleeping..."
0.35, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "WDT ISR fired, count=1"
